The '''Consortium for Advanced Research Training in Africa''' abbreviated as '''CARTA''' is a partnership involving nine [[academic institution|academic]] and four [[research institution]]s from central, western, eastern and southern Africa to strengthen research infrastructure and the management capacity of African universities. It also focus on the provision of support for doctoral training program in public and population health.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Building capacity for public and population health research in Africa|pmc=2982787 | pmid=21085517|doi=10.3402/gha.v3i0.5693|volume=3|year=2010 | last1 = Ezeh | first1 = AC | last2 = Izugbara | first2 = CO | last3 = Kabiru | first3 = CW | last4 = Fonn | first4 = S | last5 = Kahn | first5 = K | last6 = Manderson | first6 = L | last7 = Undieh | first7 = AS | last8 = Omigbodun | first8 = A | last9 = Thorogood | first9 = M}}</ref> The [[consortium]] is currently chairs by Anne Nangulu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartafrica.org/cms/board-of-management|title=Board of Management- CARTA|work=cartafica.org|accessdate=September 15, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304054528/http://www.cartafrica.org/cms/board-of-management|archivedate=March 4, 2016|df=}}</ref>
