{{no footnotes|date=January 2013}} [[File:Cvetka Ahlin.jpg|thumbnail|Cvetka Ahlin]] '''Cvetka Ahlin''' (28 November 1927, in Cologne – 30 July 1985, in Hamburg) was a Slovenian opera singer and mezzo-sopranist. Since 1951, she was the main singer of the [[Ljubljana]] Opera. From 1956 she was a singer in the Hamburg national opera, where a.o. she sang second lady to the Queen of the Night in [[The Magic Flute]] under [[Karl Böhm]] (recorded by [[Deutsche Grammophon]]). She sang in the works of [[Jules Massenet]] and [[Richard Strauss]]. In 1967, she sang as contralto in Smetana's Battered Bride with the German Opera Orchestra Berlin conducted by [[Heinrich Hollreiser]].
== Notable roles == * Charlotte in the opera [[Werther]] from Jules Massenet * Octavian in the opera [[Der Rosenkavalier]] from Richard Strauss
