'''Jugroom Fort''' is a complex of fortified buildings south-west of [[Garmsir]] in [[Helmand Province]], [[Afghanistan]], on the east bank of the [[Helmand River]]. The fort is several centuries old, and in 2007 it was used as a [[Taliban]] base.<ref>{{cite book | last=Macy | first=E. | title=Apache | publisher=[[HarperCollins]] | date=2008 | pages=239–240 | isbn=978-0-00-728817-5 }}</ref> British forces assaulted the fort on 15 January 2007. During the attack, [[Royal Marines|Royal Marine]] Lance-Corporal Mathew Ford was killed by [[friendly fire]].<ref>{{cite news | last=Norton-Taylor | first=R. | title=Poor training, confusion and friendly fire, the real story behind brave Apache rescue | newspaper=[[The Guardian]] | date=16 August 2008 | url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2008/aug/16/military.afghanistan | accessdate=8 September 2012 }}</ref> For his part in the rescue, author and Apache pilot Ed Macy was awarded the Military Cross.

